½ cup Couscous
113 g Baby Tomatoes
¼ cup Basil Pesto
28 g Baby Spinach
¼ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
1 tbsp White Wine Vinegar
tsp Salt and Pepper*

Before starting, wash and dry all produce.  Bring 2/3 cup water to a boil in a small pot or in a kettle. Add couscous and boiling water to a medium bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine. Cover and let stand for 5 min.

While couscous rehydrates, halve tomatoes.

Fluff couscous with a fork. Add tomatoes, pesto, vinegar and spinach to couscous, then stir to combine. Sprinkle Parmesan over top.